sentences: Debbie Abono (born Deborah Ann Downer; August 31, 1929 – May 16, 2010) was an American manager of death metal and thrash metal bands during the 1980s, 1990s, and early 2000s.

In honour of Abono and Ronnie James Dio (the latter who had also recently died on the same day from cancer), Machine Head's Robb Flynn recorded and released for free online a cover of Black Sabbath's "Die Young".
